Delicious! I didn't have cinnamon challah, so I used plain challah and before I added the eggs to the custard, I spiced the milk/cream/sugar mixture with lots of cinnamon, a few dashes of ground cloves, 1/4 tsp of salt, and the zest of 1 orange. (I only used 1.5Cups of sugar, per other reviewers suggestions, and it was plenty sweet.) I then added the eggs and rum-soaked raisins (bring 1/4 cup of fresh orange juice, 1/4 cup rum, 1 Tbsp of sugar, and 1/2 cup of water to simmer, add raisins, and simmer for 20 minutes to plump.). Soaked the bread in a mixing bowl for 20 minutes, stirring every once in a while. Dumped mixture into a cooking-sprayed 7-quart Dutch Oven and baked as directed. Served it with the Spiced Rum sauce (with double the rum, a dash of salt, and some extra vanilla) and vanilla ice cream. All 11 dinner guests loved it!

