Simply amazing!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! For those searching for an extraordinary finish to any meal with a simple recipe this is it. It received rave reviews by everyone at the dinner party I attended which I was responsible for preparing and bringing the desert. Even the non bread pudding eaters were very pleased with the dish. The Sara Lee Cinimon raisin bread suggestion works wonderfully and the rainins were just perfect (it looked like a lot of raisins while I was preparing the bread). I used the full amount of sugar listed in the recipe and had no complaints. This is a wonderful dish for transporting (with the sauce separate) as it holds its temperature well. The sauce held up very well thru preparing it the night before, refrigerating and reheating. A must try if you like bread pudding!!!!!!!!! The rum sauce I used was: 1/4 cup (1/2 stick) unsalted butter 1/2 cup whipping cream 1/2 cup packed dark brown sugar Pinch of salt 2 tablespoons dark rum (Makes about 1 cup): Melt butter in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat. Add cream, sugar and salt. Bring to boil, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat. Stir in rum. (Can be prepared 2 days ahead. Cover and refrigerate. Reheat over low heat, stirring constantly.)

